{"title":"Tektro becomes Bosch Antilock Brakes partner for e-bike spec","link":"https://bikerumor.com/tektro-becomes-bosch-antilock-brakes-partner-for-e-bike-spec/","date":1680011193000,"content":"<p>First developed with Magura brakes, the <a href=\"https://www.bosch-ebike.com\" target=\"_blank\">Bosch</a> Antilock Braking System for e-bikes has expanded their partnerships to include <a href=\"https://tektro-usa.com\" target=\"_blank\">Tektro</a> and <a href=\"https://trpcycling.com\" target=\"_blank\">TRP</a> models. The technology is the same, but now with more options for OEM partners. And with drivetrains now on offer, Tektro (and their high-performance TRP division) bring a lot to the table.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"tektro and bosch antilock brakes for e-bikes shown on a bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Bosch ABS system got a big update in 2022 to a smaller form factor with improved performance. It’s intended for the front brake only and pairs with (and is powered by) a Bosch e-Bike drive system.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"tektro and bosch antilock brakes for e-bikes shown on a bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-03.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It works by having a sensor monitor the speed of an additional plate mounted to the brake rotor. If it detects lockup, it’ll pulse the brake caliper much as a car’s ABS system does, keeping the wheel rotating for improved traction and control. And no endos.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>E-Bike specific forks like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/fox-awl-fork-is-a-stiffer-34mm-stanchion-fork-with-all-the-mounts-for-emtbs-and-e-suvs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fox AWL</a> have dedicated mounts for ABS systems, specifically to hold the brake controller and manage it’s wiring, though sometimes fender mounting tabs are borrowed for them, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"tektro and bosch antilock brakes for e-bikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-04.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The brake calipers are same as normal, and levers can be had with or without a sensor to trigger brake lights.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"placard showing variations of TRP and Tektro ABS systems\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tektro-e-bike-bosch-antilock-brakes-system-05.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ll offer three systems at launch later this year, two Tektro versions for city and touring bikes (which includes some lightly loaded trekking bikes popular in Europe), and a TRP version for eMTB and eATB bikes.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/tektro-becomes-bosch-antilock-brakes-partner-for-e-bike-spec/\">Tektro becomes Bosch Antilock Brakes partner for e-bike spec</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3e0529eddbe099507f21349ec893b5806aa3d00663b6dc444af781a6ec57ebd1","category":"Cycling"}